descriptionM.value: The Johnstons celebrate the holidays with candles and Christmas sweaters.

longDescriptionM.value: The Johnstons continue to celebrate the holidays with homemade candles and ugly Christmas sweaters. Plus, take an inside look at the family's clogging routine.

descriptionM.value: The Christmas episode leaves the siblings salivating over their treasures.

longDescriptionM.value: The Christmas episode leaves the siblings salivating over their treasures. Deniko is all about the bling, while Darian predicts Dariz's new trash truck will be cherished for decades. Then, Dallas shares his future plans -- like when to put a ring on it.

longDescriptionM.value: All eyes are on Darian as the kids watch her birthday party at the go-kart track. Darian may be the fastest Derrico on wheels, but Deon wants her to pump the brakes when it comes to dating. Now, the siblings weigh in with their own absurd opinions!

longDescriptionM.value: With so many rooms in this Smart Home pulling double duty, Tiffany reveals how these spaces do it all!

longDescriptionM.value: The kids unanimously agree that selling Poppy's hot cocoa could make them rich, but Derrick takes things too far with his twist on lemonade. Dallas and Denver devise their baller plan to spend $900 million. Meanwhile, everyone obsesses over smelly feet.

longDescriptionM.value: As the Derrico clan gets its first peek at the season opener, the debut of beloved Koko does not disappoint -- even if it sends Poppy's OCD into overdrive. The disco dance party is a blast to revisit -- until Daician breaks the cardinal rule of wigs.

descriptionM.value: A family hunts for a vacation home near the slopes of Mount Hood, Oregon.

longDescriptionM.value: A family of three loves the mountain activities near their home in Portland, OR, and they're ready to look for a vacation home in Government Camp, OR. They hope to find a place to host their friends within their $700,000 budget.

descriptionM.value: Guy, Simon and Justin break down the big bracket kickoff.

longDescriptionM.value: Guy Fieri, Simon Majumdar and Justin Warner break down the insanity of the Tournament of Champions big bracket kickoff. They go over each battle, check out the Randomizer categories, analyze the judges' comments and share their TOC Hot List.

descriptionM.value: Guy, Simon and Justin recap what went down in the East wild card play-in.

longDescriptionM.value: Guy Fieri, Simon Majumdar and Justin Warner meet in the studio to discuss what went down in the East wild card play-in. They examine each battle, breaking down the Randomizer categories and analyzing the judges' comments.

descriptionM.value: Host Callahan Walsh is joined by victim's advocate Monique Hudson.

longDescriptionM.value: Host Callahan Walsh is joined by Monique Hudson, a victim's advocate at the Ponca Tribe of Oklahoma's Domestic Violence Center and close friend of murder victim, Janett Reyna, who was allegedly stabbed to death by her ex, Luis Frias.

descriptionM.value: Host Callahan Walsh is joined by Josephine Wentzel.

longDescriptionM.value: Host Callahan Walsh is joined by Josephine Wentzel, whose daughter Krystal Mitchell was allegedly murdered by Raymond "RJ" McLeod in June 2016. Callahan features three new missing children, Patrick Alford Jr. plus siblings Amina and Belel Kandil.

descriptionM.value: John Walsh tracks the story of a convicted killer who twice escaped prison.

longDescriptionM.value: We know there's another capture right around the corner. Callahan digs into the case of Glen Chambers, who has been on the run for 29 years and could be anywhere.

descriptionM.value: John profiles Juan Lazaro Abrego, who may have murdered his ex-girlfriend.

longDescriptionM.value: Juan Lazaro Abrego was Elizabeth Bowie's first boyfriend, and at first his attention thrilled her. But then he became possessive. After Elizabeth backed out of the relationship, Abrego allegedly entered Elizabeth's home and strangled her to death.

descriptionM.value: Host Callahan Walsh gives an update about Jayme Closs.

longDescriptionM.value: Host Callahan Walsh gives an update about Jayme Closs, a missing child who was recovered. He's joined by Kelly Bryant, sister of Byron "BJ" Bryant, a Hampton University student who was stabbed to death in a bar brawl off campus in 2005.

descriptionM.value: Host Callahan Walsh is joined by Linda and Johnnie Quintero.

longDescriptionM.value: Host Callahan Walsh is joined by Linda and Johnnie Quintero, friends of the couple at the center of this week's main story, victim Karen Garcia who was allegedly murdered by her ex-boyfriend Salvador Vaca Garcia. Callahan recaps the story of Lori Hannah.

descriptionM.value: Callahan profiles a vet who is accused of allegedly murdering his wife.

longDescriptionM.value: In this episode, host Callahan Walsh is joined by Chyanne Paxton, whose aunt Cati Blauvelt was allegedly killed by her estranged husband, John Blauvelt. Callahan discusses the story of Rudy Fernandez and the power of social media in law enforcement.

descriptionM.value: Callahan has the latest on the Luis Frias capture.

longDescriptionM.value: Callahan has the latest on the Luis Frias capture and our new case - fugitive Lamont Stephenson on the FBI's Top 10 Most Wanted list.

descriptionM.value: Callahan Walsh discusses Lamont Stephenson's capture and the Osibin case.

longDescriptionM.value: In this episode, host Callahan Walsh discusses Lamont Stephenson's capture and talks about the Alicia Osibin case with Det. Sgt. Ian Wong of California's El Cerrito Police. Cal also covers 4 new missing children and the Frederick McLean case.

descriptionM.value: A talk with the detective in the Mike Bullinger alleged homicide case.

longDescriptionM.value: Callahan talks to the lead investigator in the Mike Bullinger alleged triple homicide case. Take a look at this security footage where he was last seen entering the Bridger-Teton National Forest. Is Bullinger out somewhere in the western wilderness?

descriptionM.value: Find America's best pizza, from ricotta and bacon to chipotle chicken.

longDescriptionM.value: Check out America's favorite pizza, featuring fresh lumps of crabmeat on top of mozzarella in Baltimore, a meat-loving ricotta, sausage and bacon pie in New York, and a fiery chipotle chicken and chorizo slice in California.

descriptionM.value: Callahan explores the case of a con man who allegedly preyed on older men.

longDescriptionM.value: Host Callahan Walsh is joined by Sgt. Richard Wehby, who's leading the investigation into the murder of Gordon Machek. He also recaps the story of child molester Chris Deininger, and a mother of one of Deininger's victims reads an impact statement.

descriptionM.value: Will Packer discusses the exciting, new changes coming this season.

longDescriptionM.value: OWN's hit-dating reality series is back! Join executive producer Will Packer as he discusses the exciting, new changes coming this season.
